To create a repository: cvs -d<directory> init

To check out the entire repository: cvs -d<repository> get .
-d<repository> can be omitted if the CVSROOT environment variable is set.

To check out a particular module:
	cd <dir_to_work>
	cvs get <module>

To check in a change of a file:
	cvs commit <file>	or	cvs ci <file>

To add a file (2 steps):
Step 1:	cvs add <file>
Step 2:	commit the file

To add a directory:
	cvs add <dir>

To remove a file:
	rm <file>
	cvs remove <file>

To import an entire source tree:
	cd <dir_to_add>
	cvs import <path_in_repository> <vendor> <init>

Get info of a file:
	cvs status <file>

Get revision history
	cvs log <file>

To see difference between a version and the local copy:
	cvs diff -r<ver> <file>

To see difference between two versions in the repository:
	cvs diff -r<ver1> -r<ver2> <file>

To find all difference between current local version and the repository:
	cvs diff

To update with the repository:
	cvs update
